  "text": "A relation is in second normal form (abbreviated 2NF) if it is in 1NF and no non-key attribute is partially dependent on any candidate key [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . In other words, no X→Y where X is a strict subset of a candidate key and Y is a non-key attribute.",
